<p>&#8216;Fixed costs did not apply to a personal injury case which had fallen out of the protocol, the Court of Appeal has asserted. In Doyle v M&#038;D Foundations &#038; Building Services Ltd, Lord Justice Phillips ruled that there was no ambiguity in an agreed court order requiring the defendant to pay costs that were &#8220;subject of detailed assessment if not agreed.&#8221; &#8216;</p>
<p><a href="https://www.lawgazette.co.uk/news/court-of-appeal-rejects-defendants-fixed-costs-challenge/5113080.article">Full Story</a></p><p>Law Society's Gazette, 11th July 2022</p><p>Source: <a href="https://www.lawgazette.co.uk">www.lawgazette.co.uk</a></p>